<b>Sega Becomes Largest Shareholder in CSK Corp.</b> - Bumper 9:21 am 06-19-01
</table></div>

<div class=itemtext>
The following is from SegaDojo:<P>  <I>A few interesting tidbits that was recently put into public (although not surprising). It seems that Sega Corp. has become the largest shareholder in CSK along being the second largest investor in NextCom KK. This news was recently posted in the Nihon Keizai Shimbun Saturday morning edition. After Isao Ohkaw, the company's former President and Chairman, passed away in March, he donated his stakes to the company. With Sega holding 4.4 million shares (or 5.9% in stake) in CSK along with 19.88 million shares of it's own company (or 12.2% in stakes), it will be very interesting to see what the financial state will be for them in the near future.</I><P>  Probably not particularly interesting for most folks out there, but this is worth noting, nonetheless.<P>  Source: <A HREF="http://www.cloudchaser.com/cc/sega/">SegaDojo</A>   <br>
