<div class=itemtext>
<br> <p align="center"><img src="http://dcmedia.ign.com/media/news2/image/japanese/010607update/sonic_in.jpg"></p>  <p>It's Sonic's tenth anniversary in Japan, and to celebrate, Sonic Team is holding a birthday party! The party is set to take place in Japan on June 23rd starting at 8:00 (in Osaka) and June 24th starting at 4:30 (in Tokyo). Those who attend will get to meet members of Sonic Team and socialize with fellow rabid fans and Sega of Japan PR reps. </p>  <p>Believe it or not, it's actually suggested that you bring a present for Sonic! Sonic Team does ask that you not bring anything too valuable, though. Those who attend will receive a special piece of Sonic merchandize which we presume will be sellable on Ebay for thousands and thousands of dollars fifty years from now.</p>  <p>We've heard that Sonic Team is hoping to hold similar events in America, although nothing has been confirmed at this point. Sega of America&#8230; how about it? </p>  <p>If you're in Japan, turn to <a href="http://www.sonicteam.com/10th_info/birthdayparty/birthdayparty.html">this page</a> for more details.</p>  <p> </p>  <p>Source: <a href="http://dreamcast.ign.com/news/35606.html">DCIGN</a></p> <br>
